Richard Walsh (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Walsh_(actor) 0 Richard Francis Evelyn Walsh (born 8 December 1952 in Lewisham, London) is an English actor, best known for playing fireman Bert "Sicknote" Quigley in the long-running ITV drama series London's Burning from 1986 to 2000. He has also appeared in other well-known British television shows, including Midsomer Murders, Doctors and Heartbeat. He is married to fellow actress Sarah Keller with one son, named James.
